cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the relationship between national funding strategies and the output of publications and patents, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are relevant due to the bibliometric analysis used in the study. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are relevant due to the focus on national funding strategies and their impact on research output. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) may also be relevant due to the potential implications of the findings for national security and innovation.
